      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Energy Ties That Bind Us</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Harry Zutz letter on paradoxical, unpatriotic sight of gas-guzzling behemoth SUV lumbering down narrow city street, adorned with American flag (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I say ''right on'' to Thomas L. Friedman for his Jan. 2 column, ''Let's Roll,'' about achieving energy independence.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I say ''right on'' to Thomas L. Friedman for his Jan. 2 column, ''Let's Roll,'' about achieving energy independence.</p>
        <p>To me, there is no more paradoxical and unpatriotic sight than a gas-guzzling behemoth (the S.U.V.), especially when navigated by a driver who is its sole occupant, lumbering down a narrow city street, proudly bearing an American flag.</p>
        <p>HARRY ZUTZ  Maplewood, N.J., Jan. 2, 2002</p>
      </block>
